subSection.paragraph:
A phytochemical study of the root of 

E. fischeriana

led to the isolation of an abietane-type diterpenoid (
2
) (
Adelakun et al., 2020
). From the same plant, nine abietane diterpenoids, fischerianoids A-C (

3 
–
5

) (
Li et al., 2020
) and 11β- hydroxy-8,14-epoxy-ent-abieta-13(15)-en-16, 12-olide (
6
) (
Wang et al., 2013
), fischeriabietane A-E (

7 
–
11

) were isolated by different research groups. It is worth noting that all these abietane diterpenoids bearing an additional five-membered lactone ring might derive from the proposed precursors of fischeriabietanes B (
8
) and C (
9
) (
Zhang et al., 2017b
). 
Wang et al. (2017a)
isolated 21 diterpenoids, including four abietane-type diterpenoids (

12 
–
15

) from 

E. fischeriana
(
Wang et al., 2017a
)

. Later, four abietane-type diterpenoids, fischeriolides A-D (

16 
–
19

), together with 11 known diterpenoids were obtained from the same plant (
Lee et al., 2016b
).

The phytochemical investigation on the roots of 

E. ebracteolata
,

obtained twelve rosane 
type
diterpenoids, ebractenoids C-E, H-J (

144 
–
149

) (
Liu et al., 2014b
), euphebracteolatin B (
150
) (
Mu et al., 2013
), ebractenoid O (
151
) (
Yu et al., 2018
), ebractenoids O–P (
152–153
) (
Bai et al., 2018
) and ebracteolatas A-B (
154–155
) (
Yuan et al., 2016
).

25 jatrophane-type diterpenoids were obtained from the whole plant of 

E. helioscopia

, including euphorbiapene A-C (

204 
–
206

) (
Chen et al., 2014a
) and secoheliospholane A (
207
) with an unusual 7,8-seco-jatrophane skeleton, 2- 
epi
-euphornin I (
208
) (
Mai et al., 2018b
), euphoscopoids A-B (

209 
–
210

) (
Hua et al., 2017
), euphoheliosnoid E (
308
) (
Geng et al., 2015
), and helioscopianoids A-Q (

211 
–
227

) (
Mai et al., 2018c
).

Two myrsinol-type diterpenoids, 3,7,14,15-tetraacetyl-5-propanoyl- 13(17)-epoxy-8,10(18)-myrsinadiene (
371
) and 3,7,10,14,15-pentaacetyl-5-butanoyl-13,17-epoxy-8-myrsinenen (
372
) were isolated from the acetone-chloroform (1:2) extract of the aerial parts of 

E. connata
(
Shadi et al., 2015
)

.

From the ethanol extract of the roots of
E. micractina, Tian et al.
got twelve diterpenoids, euphactins E-F (
419 – 420
), euphoractins F-L (
421 – 427
), and euphoractin M-N (
428 – 430
), possessing 5/6/8, 5/6/7/ 3, and 5/6/6/4 fused-ring skeletons ( Tian et al., 2013 ), respectively. Xu et al. (2014) obtained a diterpenoid secoeuphoractin ( 431 ) with a novel carbon skeleton ( Xu et al., 2014 ), and Tian et al. (2014) gained a diterpenoid euphorbactin ( 432 ) with an unprecedented 6/5/7/3 fused-ring skeleton ( Tian et al., 2014 ).

Euphorkanlide A ( 451 ), a highly modified ingenane diterpenoid, showed significant cytotoxicities against a panel of cancer cell lines (IC 50 < 5 μM) ( Yan et al., 2019 ). Three abietane diterpenoids (
3 – 5
) showed selective inhibitory potency against certain human tumor cell lines with IC 50 values ranging from 8.50 ± 0.13 to 35.52 ± 0.08 μM ( Li et al., 2020 ). Three diterpenoids, tigliane ( 407 ), ingenane ( 181 ) and abietane ( 36 ), were tested for their cytotoxicity against five cancer cell lines (A549, MCF-7, HepG2, HeLa and P388), with IC 50 values in the range 6.64–42.86 μM ( Yang et al., 2014 ). A lathyrane-type diterpenoid ( 321 ) showed strong cytotoxicity to 786-O human kidney cells and HepG2 liver cancer cells, with IC 50 value of 9.43 μM and 13.22 μM, respectively ( Wang et al., 2018b ). An ent -abietane-type diterpenoid ( 37 ) showed cytotoxicity against the two cell lines with IC 50 values of 19.5 μM (NCI–H460) and 18.6 μM (MCF-7), while for cis -platinum (a positive control) exhibiting IC 50 values of 29.7 μM (NCI–H460) and 27.7 μM (MCF-7). A rosane-type diterpenoid ( 150 ) showed weak inhibition of tumor growth with an IC 50 value of 14.90 ± 2.01 μg ( Mu et al., 2013 ). An ingenane ( 178 ) showed significant cytotoxicity against A549 with an IC 50 value of 3.35 μg/mL ( Wang et al., 2013 ). Two norlathyrane diterpenoids, ekanpenoids A and B, exhibited potent cytotoxic activities against the HeLa and Hep-G2 cell lines with IC 50 values ranging from 3.6 to 9.7 μM ( Zhang et al., 2013 ). A cembrane diterpenoid, ()-(1 S )-15-hydroxy-18-carboxycembrene ( 156 ), showed cytotoxic activity against five human cancer cell lines including HeLa, PC-3, HT1080, A375-S2 and MDA231, with IC 50 values of 35.3 ± 3.6, 53.9 ± 6.2, 37.3 ± 2.0, 28.7 ± 3.8 and 43.5 ± 5.1 μM, respectively ( Hou et al., 2013 ). Euphordraculoates B ( 453 ), which possesses a novel carbon skeleton, showed cytotoxic activities on all the tested cells, Caco2, HT29, and HCT116, with IC 50 values of 10.97, 31.78, and 42.58 μM, respectively ( Wang et al., 2017b ). A tigliane-type diterpenoid ester, 4, 20-dideoxy-4 α -phorbol-12 β -acetate-13 α -isobutyrate ( 405 ), exhibited weak cytotoxic effects against promyelocytic leukemia HL60 cells, with IC 50 values of 97 μM ( Benmerache et al., 2017 ). An ingenane-type diterpenoid ( 180 ) was found to be cytotoxic against A375 and HMCB cells with IC 50 values of 15.37 ± 2.6 μM and 15.62 ± 1.89 μM, respectively ( Fallahian et al., 2017 ). A rosane-type diterpenoid ( 154 ) exhibited moderate cytotoxic effects against HL-60, A549, SMMC-7721, MCF-7, and SW480 with IC 50 values of 17.5, 11.0, 16.8, 17.5, and 18.0 μM ( Yuan et al., 2016 ), respectively. Euphorikanin A ( 447 ), an unprecedented diterpenoid lactone possessing a 5/6/7/3-fused tetracyclic ring skeleton, exhibited moderate cytotoxicity against two human tumor cell lines HeLa and NCI-446 ( Fei et al., 2016 ). An ent -atisane-type diterpenoid ( 78 ) showed significant inhibitory activity on human breast cancer MCF-7 cells with IC 50 values of 10.0 μM ( Kuang et al., 2016 ). Two ent -atisanes, 80 and 81 , showed inhibitory effects against MCF-7 cells with IC 50 values of 23.21 and 15.42 μM ( Wang et al., 2016b ). Two myrsinol-type diterpenoids (
371 – 372
) exhibited moderate inhibitory effects, with IC 50 values of 24.53 ± 3.39 and 26.67 ± 1.41 μM against MDA-MB cell line, and 37.73 ± 3.41 and 34.57 ± 2.12 μM against MCF-7 cell line, respectively ( Shadi et al., 2015 ). An ent -isopimarane-type diterpenoid ( 115 ) showed cytotoxic activity against the A549 cancer cell line with an IC 50 value of 13.033 μg/mL ( Rushangul et al., 2018 ).

Two ingenane-type diterpenoids (
168 – 169
) exhibited potent activities against HIV-1, with IC 50 values of 2.7 ± 1.3 and 1.1 ± 0.3 nM, respectively ( Huang et al., 2019 ). Two abietane type diterpenoids (
33 – 34
) exhibited significant anti-HIV activities, with EC 50 values of 3.58 ± 0.31 μM (SI = 8.6) and 7.40 ± 0.94 μM (SI = 10.3), respectively ( Zhao et al., 2014 ). Compound 431 showed activity against HIV-1 replication with an IC 50 value of 1.76 ± 0.61 μM ( Xu et al., 2014 ). A diterpenoid ( 411 ) showed activity against HIV-1 replication, with IC 50 and SI values of 28.6 ± 0.8 μM and 86.1, respectively ( Tian et al., 2014 ). An atisane ( 77 ) showed moderate anti-HIV-1 activities, with EC 50 values of 34 μM (SI = 2.3) ( Yan et al., 2018 ). Lower diterpenoids show much better anti-HIV-1 activity than higher diterpenoids. Two ingenane-type diterpenoids (
174 – 175
), showed moderate activity against RSV virus, both with IC 50 values of 25 μM and selective indices of 1.0 and 3.2, respectively ( Huang et al., 2014 ). An ent- atisane-type diterpenoid ( 86 ) showed antiviral activities against human rhinovirus 3, with an IC 50 value of 90.35 μM ( Wang et al., 2018a ). A rosane-type diterpenoid ( 132 ) showed significant potent inhibitory activity on EBV with an EC 50 value of 5.4 μM similar to the positive control ( + )-rutamarin (EC 50 = 5.4 μM) ( Liu et al., 2017a ).

Nine atisane (
60 – 68
) and a kaurane-type diterpenoids ( 119 ) showed the inhibition of nitric oxide (NO) generation in lipopolysaccharide-induced murine microglial BV-2 cells ( Liang et al., 2019 ). Three lathyrane-type diterpenoids (
314 – 316
) displayed inhibitory effects on NO production, with IC 50 values of 2.6–26.0 μM ( Zhang et al., 2019 ). Two ingenane-type (
170 – 171
), two kaurane-type (
120 – 121
) and an abietane-type ( 29 ) diterpenoids were examined for their inhibition of NO generation in lipopolysaccharide-stimulated BV-2 cells, with IC 50 values lower than 40 μM ( Wang et al., 2019a ). Three jatrophane-type diterpenoids (
204 – 206
) showed inhibitory activities on LPS-induced NO production in BV-2 cells ( Chen et al., 2014a ). A lathyrane type diterpenoid ( 326 ) were found to inhibit NO production in LPS-induced RAW 264.7 macrophages, with IC 50 value of 47.9 ± 4.5 μM ( Lee et al., 2018 ). A rosane-type diterpenoid ( 150 ) exhibited significant inhibition of NO production in lipopolysaccharide-induced RAW 264.7 macrophages, with IC 50 values of 2.76 μM ( Mu et al., 2013 ). Two pepluane-type (
391 – 392
) and a paraliane-type ( 399 ) diterpenoids displayed moderate inhibitory effects on NO production, with IC 50 values ranging from 29.9 to 38.3 μM ( Wan et al., 2016a ). An abietane-type diterpenoid ( 25 ) exhibited significant inhibitory activities on lipopolysaccharide (LPS)-induced NO production in RAW 264.7 macrophages with IC 50 values of 1.97 μM ( Liu et al., 2016c ).

A jatrophane diterpenoid ( 230 ) strongly inhibited the drug-efflux activity of the primary ABC transporter CaCdr1p with an IC 50 value of 31.7 ± 2.9 ( Rawal et al., 2014 ). Two jatrophane-type diterpenoids (
241 – 242
) possessed MDR reversal activities, with IC 50 values of 5.0 ± 0.8 μM and 5.2 ± 2.0 μM, which were as good as those of verapamil (IC 50 value of 4.7 ± 0.6 μM) ( Hasan et al., 2019 ). A diterpenoid ( 436 ) showed significant P-glycoprotein inhibitory activity compared with the positive control (cyclosporine A) ( Mai et al., 2018a ). Compound 404 exhibited remarkable multidrug resistance regulation at 20 μM ( Redei et al., 2018 ). Two jatrophane-type diterpenoids (
297 – 298
) showed moderate inhibitory effects on P-glycoprotein with IC 50 values of 8.55 ± 3.21 μM and 8.72 ± 3.45 μM respectively. In the experiment conducted, cyclosporine A (CsA), a well-known inhibitor of Pgp function, was taken as a reference inhibitor (IC 50 of 3.37 ± 1.39 μM) ( Lanzotti et al., 2015 ).

Only seven compounds have the activity of glucose metabolism regulation activity. Two ingol-type diterpenoids (
184
, 
187
) exhibited inhibitory activities against mouse 11β- HSD1 with IC 
50
values of 12.0 and 6.4 μM, respectively (
Qi et al., 2014
). Three highly modified cembranoids, quorumolides A C (

448 
–
450

) showed inhibitory activity on 11β- HSD1 (
Qi et al., 2018
). Two diterpenoids, rhamnofolane (
166
) and pimarene (
118
) showed moderate inhibitory effects against α- glucosidase in an 
in vitro
bioassay, suggesting that diterpenoids could be potential hypoglycemic drugs (
Wei et al., 2018b
).

Two cyclomyrsinol-type (

348 
–
349

) (
Ghanadian et al., 2013a
) and a jatropholane-type (
299
) (
Yang et al., 2013
) diterpenoids showed vasoactive activity.

A cyclomyrsinol-type (
359
) (
Ghanadian et al., 2013b
) and a novel skeletal 
type
(
439
) diterpenoids (
Wan et al., 2016b
) showed the immunomodulatory activity.

A jatrophane-type diterpenoid (
283
) showed nanomolar antimalarial activity (
Zhou et al., 2016
).
